her off to one molecule

00:36:01.260 --> 00:36:06.120 align:middle line:84%
in particular, C-8,
the molecule in Teflon

00:36:06.120 --> 00:36:08.660 align:middle line:84%
that stops food from
sticking to pans.

00:36:08.660 --> 00:36:11.430 align:middle line:84%
>> When I went back
to work the first day,

00:36:11.430 --> 00:36:13.980 align:middle line:84%
I went to the locker and I
found the paper laying there.

00:36:13.980 --> 00:36:17.190 align:middle line:84%
I picked it up and I
began reading about it.

00:36:17.190 --> 00:36:21.420 align:middle line:84%
It was talking about how
the rats were fed the C-8

00:36:21.420 --> 00:36:25.600 align:middle line:84%
and what deformities that
it had around their face,

00:36:25.600 --> 00:36:28.940 align:middle line:84%
and I thought, that
sounds just like Becky.

00:36:28.940 --> 00:36:30.690 align:middle line:84%
>> It was very similar
to what Bucky had.

00:36:30.690 --> 00:36:31.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:36:31.530 --> 00:36:34.588 align:middle line:84%
Very similar, almost
identical to what he had.

00:36:34.588 --> 00:36:36.630 align:middle line:84%
That's why I knew that
there was something wrong.

00:36:36.630 --> 00:36:40.050 align:middle line:90%
That's why it connect.

00:36:40.050 --> 00:36:43.260 align:middle line:84%
>> The scientific studies
Suzanne Bailey found had been

00:36:43.260 --> 00:36:46.590 align:middle line:84%
conducted by a
subcontractor of DuPont.

00:36:46.590 --> 00:36:50.490 align:middle line:84%
It studied baby rats whose
mothers were exposed to C-8.

00:36:50.490 --> 00:36:52.530 align:middle line:84%
They developed
abnormal eye lenses.

00:36:52.530 --> 00:36:55.296 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:36:55.296 --> 00:36:56.680 align:middle line:90%


00:36:56.680 --> 00:37:00.330 align:middle line:84%
I immediately walked out that
door, went down to medical,

00:37:00.330 --> 00:37:02.280 align:middle line:84%
and I said, is this
what's wrong with my baby?

00:37:02.280 --> 00:37:03.780 align:middle line:90%
Oh, no, no, no.

00:37:03.780 --> 00:37:05.990 align:middle line:84%
Nothing on this
plant will hurt you.

00:37:05.990 --> 00:37:07.313 align:middle line:90%
That was the motto.

00:37:07.313 --> 00:37:08.480 align:middle line:90%
That's what they always say.

00:37:08.480 --> 00:37:09.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:37:09.400 --> 00:37:11.031 align:middle line:90%
>> Nothing here will hurt you.

00:37:11.031 --> 00:37:13.800 align:middle line:90%


00:37:13.800 --> 00:37:17.760 align:middle line:84%
>> But in the meantime, DuPont
was secretly investigating

00:37:17.760 --> 00:37:20.520 align:middle line:84%
the pregnant women
working in their factory.

00:37:20.520 --> 00:37:22.920 align:middle line:84%
Two out of seven children
born to the factory

00:37:22.920 --> 00:37:26.490 align:middle line:84%
workers had facial
deformities like Bucky.

00:37:26.490 --> 00:37:29.490 align:middle line:84%
Shortly after, DuPont
decided to transfer

00:37:29.490 --> 00:37:31.260 align:middle line:84%
Suzanne Bailey
and her colleagues

00:37:31.260 --> 00:37:32.400 align:middle line:90%
to other departments.

00:37:32.400 --> 00:37:36.960 align:middle line:90%


00:37:36.960 --> 00:37:40.800 align:middle line:84%
At the time, Kenton Wamsley
also worked in the manufacturing

00:37:40.800 --> 00:37:43.530 align:middle line:90%
department of Teflon.

00:37:43.530 --> 00:37:46.610 align:middle line:84%
He remembers the discussion
he had with his manager.

00:37:46.610 --> 00:37:49.410 align:middle line:84%
>> He said, can we send all
the women home out of Teflon?

00:37:49.410 --> 00:37:51.170 align:middle line:90%
All of them.

00:37:51.170 --> 00:37:52.340 align:middle line:90%
He said, oh, don't worry.

00:37:52.340 --> 00:37:55.280 align:middle line:84%
It won't hurt the
men, just the women.

00:37:55.280 --> 00:37:59.460 align:middle line:84%
We feel that it
can cause trouble.

00:37:59.460 --> 00:38:03.740 align:middle line:90%
So I thought, won't hurt me.

00:38:03.740 --> 00:38:06.960 align:middle line:84%
>> Kenton Wamsley
was a lab technician.

00:38:06.960 --> 00:38:09.920 align:middle line:90%
He handled C-8 for 30 years.

00:38:09.920 --> 00:38:13.940 align:middle line:84%
>> Breathed the fumes from them,
all the samples we breathe.

00:38:13.940 --> 00:38:17.490 align:middle line:84%
But we just-- at
the time, we thought

00:38:17.490 --> 00:38:21.860 align:middle line:84%
DuPont would take care
of us, so I just did

00:38:21.860 --> 00:38:25.210 align:middle line:90%
my jobs for years and years.

00:38:25.210 --> 00:38:29.720 align:middle line:84%
And we didn't realize our
health was an issue then.

00:38:29.720 --> 00:38:34.800 align:middle line:84%
Surgeon diagnosed
me as having cancer.

00:38:34.800 --> 00:38:37.511 align:middle line:84%
They had to take all of my
rectum, part of my colon.

00:38:37.511 --> 00:38:38.636 align:middle line:90%
>> They're giving you that?

00:38:38.636 --> 00:38:40.070 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, for every five years.

00:38:40.070 --> 00:38:43.270 align:middle line:90%


00:38:43.270 --> 00:38:46.250 align:middle line:84%
>> Now Kenton Wamsley has
to live with an ostonomy bag

00:38:46.250 --> 00:38:49.010 align:middle line:90%
attached to his stomach.

00:38:49.010 --> 00:38:51.570 align:middle line:90%
He changes it day and night.

00:38:51.570 --> 00:38:53.880 align:middle line:84%
At the factory, he
worked in a team

00:38:53.880 --> 00:38:57.900 align:middle line:90%
with three other technicians.

00:38:57.900 --> 00:39:01.410 align:middle line:84%
>> My buddies, people I really
loved, seen them every day,

00:39:01.410 --> 00:39:03.850 align:middle line:84%
cared about them, those
guys, they're all dead,

00:39:03.850 --> 00:39:05.400 align:middle line:90%
and I should have been.

00:39:05.400 --> 00:39:07.880 align:middle line:90%
They didn't even see retirement.

00:39:07.880 --> 00:39:10.760 align:middle line:90%
None of them.

00:39:10.760 --> 00:39:13.910 align:middle line:84%
>> Wamsley and his colleagues
were never warned about

00:39:13.910 --> 00:39:16.880 align:middle line:90%
the risks of C-8.

00:39:16.880 --> 00:39:19.580 align:middle line:84%
However, we procured a
confidential document

00:39:19.580 --> 00:39:21.430 align:middle line:90%
from DuPont.

00:39:21.430 --> 00:39:26.740 align:middle line:90%
It's dated 1982, 34 years ago.

00:39:26.740 --> 00:39:30.820 align:middle line:84%
In it, Mr. Carr, the medical
director at the time,

00:39:30.820 --> 00:39:34.570 align:middle line:84%
expresses concern about the
consequences of C-8 retained

00:39:34.570 --> 00:39:38.410 align:middle line:90%
in the blood of employees.

00:39:38.410 --> 00:39:41.590 align:middle line:84%
He specifically recommends
that practical steps be

00:39:41.590 --> 00:39:43.570 align:middle line:90%
taken to reduce this exposure.

00:39:43.570 --> 00:39:47.260 align:middle line:90%


00:39:47.260 --> 00:39:51.100 align:middle line:84%
>> "All employees, not
just Teflon area workers,

00:39:51.100 --> 00:39:52.300 align:middle line:90%
are exposed."

00:39:52.300 --> 00:39:54.670 align:middle line:84%
So rather than do anything,
they just wrote it out.

00:39:54.670 --> 00:39:58.770 align:middle line:90%


00:39:58.770 --> 00:40:01.500 align:middle line:90%
I never seen a letter like that.

00:40:01.500 --> 00:40:02.550 align:middle line:90%
I'm mad.

00:40:02.550 --> 00:40:04.590 align:middle line:90%
You can see why.

00:40:04.590 --> 00:40:07.540 align:middle line:84%
We could have
prevented a lot of lies

00:40:07.540 --> 00:40:11.290 align:middle line:84%
if they wouldn't told
us there's a problem.

00:40:11.290 --> 00:40:14.990 align:middle line:90%
Why'd they cover it up?

00:40:14.990 --> 00:40:17.970 align:middle line:90%
Why'd they lie?

00:40:17.970 --> 00:40:21.310 align:middle line:84%
Why didn't they
have us protected?

00:40:21.310 --> 00:40:22.110 align:middle line:90%
Too costly?

00:40:22.110 --> 00:40:26.560 align:middle line:90%


00:40:26.560 --> 00:40:29.350 align:middle line:84%
>> We tracked down Bruce
Carr, DuPont's former medical

00:40:29.350 --> 00:40:31.790 align:middle line:90%
director.

00:40:31.790 --> 00:40:34.080 align:middle line:84%
He is now enjoying a
peaceful retirement

00:40:34.080 --> 00:40:38.510 align:middle line:84%
by the ocean, far
from Parkersburg.

00:40:38.510 --> 00:40:42.210 align:middle line:84%
>> I have a document of 1982
showing that you are aware that

00:40:42.210 --> 00:40:44.390 align:middle line:90%
C-8 was toxic for workers.

00:40:44.390 --> 00:40:47.040 align:middle line:84%
Why have you not told them
the truth at that time?

00:40:47.040 --> 00:40:48.470 align:middle line:90%
>> They were all told the truth.

00:40:48.470 --> 00:40:50.690 align:middle line:84%
They were told everything
we knew at the time.

00:40:50.690 --> 00:40:51.565 align:middle line:90%
>> Actually, no.

00:40:51.565 --> 00:40:52.940 align:middle line:84%
I have interviewed
some employees

00:40:52.940 --> 00:40:54.920 align:middle line:84%
and they were not
aware of anything.

00:40:54.920 --> 00:40:57.950 align:middle line:84%
>> We told employees everything
we knew as soon as we knew it.

00:40:57.950 --> 00:41:00.380 align:middle line:84%
You go back to
1982, you're trying

00:41:00.380 --> 00:41:04.320 align:middle line:84%
to do reconstructionist
history, and you can't do that.

00:41:04.320 --> 00:41:07.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Why have you not
protected your employees?

00:41:07.980 --> 00:41:09.344 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

00:41:09.344 --> 00:41:12.190 align:middle line:90%


00:41:12.190 --> 00:41:16.020 align:middle line:84%
>> DuPont would not only put
their employees in danger,

00:41:16.020 --> 00:41:21.890 align:middle line:84%
once again, tens of thousands
of people would be affected.

00:41:21.890 --> 00:41:26.080 align:middle line:84%
They live up to 70 kilometers
away from the factory.

00:41:26.080 --> 00:41:31.190 align:middle line:84%
One man would discover
this, a bit by accident.

00:41:31.190 --> 00:41:33.030 align:middle line:90%
Joe Kiger.

00:41:33.030 --> 00:41:36.420 align:middle line:84%
On October 31, 2000,
he receives a letter

00:41:36.420 --> 00:41:40.080 align:middle line:84%
from the municipality concerning
the quality of the tap water.

00:41:40.080 --> 00:41:41.610 align:middle line:90%
It mentions C-8.

00:41:41.610 --> 00:41:44.280 align:middle line:84%
>> I was sitting in my courtyard
and the wife was watering

00:41:44.280 --> 00:41:47.870 align:middle line:84%
the flowers, and we got
our water bill in the mail,

00:41:47.870 --> 00:41:52.170 align:middle line:84%
and with that bill,
came a letter.

00:41:52.170 --> 00:41:54.510 align:middle line:84%
It's like, you get form
letters all the time.

00:41:54.510 --> 00:41:57.120 align:middle line:84%
So you look, that's all, OK,
bang, and you put it over

00:41:57.120 --> 00:41:59.203 align:middle line:84%
and you don't think about
it, next thing you know,

00:41:59.203 --> 00:42:00.260 align:middle line:90%
you throw it away.

00:42:00.260 --> 00:42:02.130 align:middle line:84%
And that's basically
what this was.

00:42:02.130 --> 00:42:06.660 align:middle line:84%
It just caught my attention and
I started reading through it,

00:42:06.660 --> 00:42:09.900 align:middle line:84%
and then the flags
started popping up.

00:42:09.900 --> 00:42:15.470 align:middle line:84%
First of all, what was C-8 here,
which is used by DuPont Works.

00:42:15.470 --> 00:42:18.230 align:middle line:84%
What's DuPont have
to do with our water?

00:42:18.230 --> 00:42:20.750 align:middle line:90%


00:42:20.750 --> 00:42:24.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Joe Kiger sought
clarification on the matter.

00:42:24.220 --> 00:42:26.690 align:middle line:84%
>> I called DuPont
to try to find out,

00:42:26.690 --> 00:42:30.800 align:middle line:84%
so they put me in touch with
a guy, a gentleman named Mr.

00:42:30.800 --> 00:42:34.280 align:middle line:84%
Kennedy, and I said, you know,
I'd like to know more about

00:42:34.280 --> 00:42:35.455 align:middle line:90%
this C-8 issue.

00:42:35.455 --> 00:42:36.830 align:middle line:84%
He's just telling
me it's nothing

00:42:36.830 --> 00:42:41.780 align:middle line:84%
to worry about, about it was
just a byproduct of Teflon

00:42:41.780 --> 00:42:43.870 align:middle line:84%
and it wasn't anything
to worry about.

00:42:43.870 --> 00:42:45.680 align:middle line:90%
And he was flat out lying to me.

00:42:45.680 --> 00:42:46.580 align:middle line:90%
I could tell that.

00:42:46.580 --> 00:42:49.370 align:middle line:90%


00:42:49.370 --> 00:42:53.930 align:middle line:84%
>> To get to the bottom of
it, he takes DuPont to court.

00:42:53.930 --> 00:42:56.210 align:middle line:84%
After a long legal
battle, the judge

00:42:56.210 --> 00:43:02.130 align:middle line:84%
forces the company to declassify
their internal studies on C-8.

00:43:02.130 --> 00:43:04.600 align:middle line:84%
Joe Kiger discovers the
truth behind the factory

00:43:04.600 --> 00:43:06.670 align:middle line:90%
at Parkersburg.

00:43:06.670 --> 00:43:09.250 align:middle line:84%
For decades, they've
been dumping C-8 waste

00:43:09.250 --> 00:43:11.900 align:middle line:90%
into the river.

00:43:11.900 --> 00:43:16.370 align:middle line:84%
To make things worse,
DuPont has known since 1984

00:43:16.370 --> 00:43:20.300 align:middle line:84%
that the molecules spread
into the region's tap water.

00:43:20.300 --> 00:43:24.500 align:middle line:84%
The company found astronomical
levels in public taps,

00:43:24.500 --> 00:43:27.350 align:middle line:84%
up to 50 times the
limit of toxicity

00:43:27.350 --> 00:43:29.510 align:middle line:84%
according to the US
Environmental Protection

00:43:29.510 --> 00:43:31.220 align:middle line:90%
Agency.

00:43:31.220 --> 00:43:34.406 align:middle line:84%
>> That was 1984 and we
didn't come out till 2000.

00:43:34.406 --> 00:43:36.200 align:middle line:90%
>> So 16 years.

00:43:36.200 --> 00:43:39.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, before we even
hit them up about it.

00:43:39.320 --> 00:43:42.230 align:middle line:84%
And they chose-- as
you see right here,

00:43:42.230 --> 00:43:45.930 align:middle line:84%
they chose not to do
anything about it.

00:43:45.930 --> 00:43:48.590 align:middle line:84%
And they knew what was
coming with the liabilities

00:43:48.590 --> 00:43:49.910 align:middle line:90%
if they got caught.

00:43:49.910 --> 00:43:52.550 align:middle line:84%
They were trying to
slide under the radar.

00:43:52.550 --> 00:43:55.520 align:middle line:84%
People trusted
DuPont for so long.

00:43:55.520 --> 00:43:58.580 align:middle line:84%
They have done nothing
but lie for years

00:43:58.580 --> 00:44:00.620 align:middle line:84%
to people about what
this stuff's all about.

00:44:00.620 --> 00:44:04.070 align:middle line:84%
There's sick people out here
because of what they've done.

00:44:04.070 --> 00:44:08.740 align:middle line:84%
There's people dying because
of what they've done.

00:44:08.740 --> 00:44:12.910 align:middle line:84%
>> During all these years, more
than 70,000 people have been

00:44:12.910 --> 00:44:15.940 align:middle line:90%
drinking contaminated water.

00:44:15.940 --> 00:44:20.020 align:middle line:84%
In 2011, both scientific
research and the US justice

00:44:20.020 --> 00:44:21.970 align:middle line:84%
system established
that C-8 could

00:44:21.970 --> 00:44:27.310 align:middle line:84%
cause six diseases, thyroid
disorder, high cholesterol,

00:44:27.310 --> 00:44:32.170 align:middle line:84%
ulcerative colitis, high
blood pressure, kidney cancer,

00:44:32.170 --> 00:44:33.265 align:middle line:90%
or testicular cancer.

00:44:33.265 --> 00:44:36.760 align:middle line:90%


00:44:36.760 --> 00:44:43.280 align:middle line:84%
Today, 3,500 people in the
Parkersburg region are ill.

00:44:43.280 --> 00:44:46.630 align:middle line:84%
They've all filed
complaints against DuPont.

00:44:46.630 --> 00:44:49.015 align:middle line:84%
This is the case for
Earl and Gwen Botkin.

00:44:49.015 --> 00:44:52.366 align:middle line:90%


00:44:52.366 --> 00:44:58.346 align:middle line:84%
>> I've had ulcerative
colitis for about 17 years,

00:44:58.346 --> 00:45:01.100 align:middle line:84%
and it's about killed
me a couple of times.

00:45:01.100 --> 00:45:06.980 align:middle line:84%
I still have thyroid problem,
and I have high cholesterol,

00:45:06.980 --> 00:45:10.250 align:middle line:84%
and those are all
associated with C-8.

00:45:10.250 --> 00:45:12.500 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:45:12.500 --> 00:45:16.520 align:middle line:84%
>> Today, Earl Botkin
doesn't have a colon anymore.

00:45:16.520 --> 00:45:19.380 align:middle line:84%
He too is living
with an ostonomy bag.

00:45:19.380 --> 00:45:21.380 align:middle line:84%
>> All of a sudden, you
don't function normally.

00:45:21.380 --> 00:45:23.950 align:middle line:84%
You have your bowel
movement on your side.

00:45:23.950 --> 00:45:28.430 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I'll
live with until I die.

00:45:28.430 --> 00:45:31.995 align:middle line:90%
And there's not any--

00:45:31.995 --> 00:45:35.660 align:middle line:84%
not any hope that
that's going to change.

00:45:35.660 --> 00:45:38.810 align:middle line:84%
It controls where
I go, what I do,

00:45:38.810 --> 00:45:41.780 align:middle line:84%
and what I eat,
and just controls

00:45:41.780 --> 00:45:44.820 align:middle line:90%
a lot of things in my life.

00:45:44.820 --> 00:45:49.620 align:middle line:84%
But anyway, I
lived through that.

00:45:49.620 --> 00:45:52.560 align:middle line:90%
